    "summary": "Avocat aux barreaux de Bruxelles et de Paris, je pratique le droit de la concurrence fran\u00e7ais et europ\u00e9en depuis 1992, en anglais et en fran\u00e7ais, tant en contentieux qu'en conseil. Ma pratique inclut les programmes de compliance, les aides d'Etat, les pratiques anticoncurrentielles, ainsi que le contr\u00f4le des concentrations\n\nJ'enseigne \u00e9galement le droit de la concurrence \u00e0 Paris 2 Panth\u00e9on-Assas (M2/MBA de droit et management des affaires), le droit international des affaires \u00e0 Nanterre (Master Juriste europ\u00e9en des affaires) et j'anime un s\u00e9minaire sur les aides d'Etat \u00e0 HEC.\n\n***\nAdmitted to the Paris and Brussels bar, I work in the field of French and EU competition law since 1992, both in French and English, both as counsellor and as litigator.  My practice encompasses compliance programmes, State aids, antitrust and merger control.\n\nI also lecture in competition law at Paris 2 Panth\u00e9on Assas University and in international business law at Paris Ouest Nanterre University, and I give a seminar on State aid issues at HEC Paris.\n\n\nAcademic:\n\n1988 - LL.B summa cum laude, St-Louis, Brussels\n1992 - LL.M cum laude, Louvain (Belgium)\n2000 - Post-Graduate Diploma in Competition Law, King's College London\nSince 2008: Director of Studies, Paris 2 Panth\u00e9on-Assas (lecturer in antitrust law)\nSince 2009: Lecturer in State aid law and International Business Law, University of Nanterre (Paris)\n\nProfessional:\n\n- Admitted to the Brussels and Paris Bars\n- 1991-1992 : Trainee, Legal Service, European Commission (Brussels)\n- 1992-1995 : Associate, Lafleur Brown Canadian law firm (Brussels)\n- 1995-2000 : Associate, Jeantet & Associ\u00e9s (Paris)\n- 2000-2002 : Senior Associate, then Partner as from April 2001, Herbert Smith (Paris)\n- 2002-2005 : Partner, Clifford Chance (Paris)\n- 2005-2013 : Partner, Hogan & Hartson (then Hogan Lovells as from 2010), Paris\n- 2013-2015 : Partner, Reed Smith (Paris)\n- 2015-today : Partner, DS Avocats (Paris and Brussels)\n\nFrench, English, Dutch",
